Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with Helios head symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Agloumbrotos. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0038.22.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0835)
